        This is our fort.

00:42.209 --> 00:45.377
        Whoops, I missed.

00:45.379 --> 00:47.312
   Aw, looks like
 we're out of ammo.

00:47.314 --> 00:51.083
    That means it's time for
       my birthday party.

00:51.085 --> 00:54.887
              Who, me? Yes, me.
  Couldn't be. It's my birthday!

00:54.889 --> 00:57.056
                 [ Humming ]

00:57.058 --> 01:02.227
          I invited everybody --
      Belson and Percy, Mavis --

01:02.229 --> 01:03.262
               oh, and Nathan.

01:03.264 --> 01:05.597
Oh, well, I'm excited too.

01:05.599 --> 01:09.635
    Uh, yeah. Me and Jeff are
   definitely gonna be there.

01:12.540 --> 01:14.406
       Oh, where are they?

01:14.408 --> 01:16.341
I though we had more decorations
         from last year.

01:16.343 --> 01:18.544
        Oh, look at this!

01:18.546 --> 01:19.945
              Chad!

01:19.947 --> 01:22.748
 You'll never guess what I found
         in the garage.

01:22.750 --> 01:25.050
        It's all your old
     Chozo the Clown stuff.

01:25.052 --> 01:27.252
  Look at this! Oh, you should
    perform it for the party.

01:27.254 --> 01:30.622
I don't know, man. It was, like,
one class at Gleverly Community

01:30.624 --> 01:33.292
years ago, and it's a big reason
  why I gave it up.

01:33.294 --> 01:34.927
        Oh, my goodness!

01:34.929 --> 01:38.230
   There's the brown balloons
        and brown chairs

01:38.232 --> 01:39.731
     and brown tablecloths,

01:39.733 --> 01:42.468
     and everything's brown,
       just like I wanted.

01:42.470 --> 01:44.736
         I'm impressed.
    You really went all out.

01:44.738 --> 01:47.639
Oh, it was no sweat. Anything
for my birthday boy.

01:47.641 --> 01:50.709
Clarence, you want to help set
up and put out some chips?

01:50.711 --> 01:53.045
              Yes.

01:53.047 --> 01:55.314
     Just put these in here.
          Snacks! Let me at 'em.

01:55.316 --> 01:57.149
      Upbupbupbup! Unh-unh!
         Not yet, Sumo.

01:57.151 --> 01:59.952
 We've got to make sure there's
enough for all the other guests.

01:59.954 --> 02:01.320
                    Why?
               You mean Jeff?

02:01.322 --> 02:04.223
Jeff and all our other friends
  who's gonna come.

02:04.225 --> 02:06.325
  Guys! Somebody help, please!

02:06.327 --> 02:07.993
 I got you, my Chad.

02:07.995 --> 02:11.430
 Did he forget that no one else
  has ever come to his parties?

02:11.432 --> 02:13.932
                I don't know.
       I-I think he's in denial.

02:13.934 --> 02:16.502
   Maybe we should just give him
               his gifts now,

02:16.504 --> 02:18.904
          and then he won't even
              think of friends.

02:18.906 --> 02:20.005
              Yeah!

02:20.007 --> 02:21.173
 I'm one year older

02:21.175 --> 02:23.609
and one year stronger.

02:23.611 --> 02:25.344
   Whoa! Nice work, Clarence.

02:25.346 --> 02:28.347
Ooh! Hello, mystery package.

02:28.349 --> 02:31.617
You know, Clarence, this present
 means you won't have to ask me

02:31.619 --> 02:33.485
          for a ride to
      Jeff's house anymore.

02:33.487 --> 02:35.954
Oh. Is it a little helicopter?

02:35.956 --> 02:39.958
       What? No, Clarence.
 What are you talking about? No.

02:39.960 --> 02:42.928
     Cool! Dude, you got a bike.
         Oh, n--, I...

02:42.930 --> 02:44.830
           Oh, Sumo --

02:44.832 --> 02:47.599
 What? Sumo? A bike?
 Could you imagine?

02:47.601 --> 02:50.502
I'd be riding all around and,
like, giving you guys

02:50.504 --> 02:52.037
high-fives and stuff.

02:52.039 --> 02:53.772
   Yeah, well, that's definitely
             gonna happen later,

02:53.774 --> 02:55.641
     'cause that is a b --
                 Okay.

02:55.643 --> 02:58.010
     Uh, Clarence, why don't you
             open our presents?

02:58.012 --> 02:59.511
      Oh, good idea, Jeff.

02:59.513 --> 03:02.014
  Uh, you boys do that while I
    move this somewhere else.

03:02.016 --> 03:04.983
Well, I didn't want to open
anything until all my guests

03:04.985 --> 03:06.952
  got here, but...

03:06.954 --> 03:09.721
Ahh, Jeff! You made me
   a birthday pie?

03:09.723 --> 03:12.558
       Oh, it was nothing.
         Happy birthday!

03:12.560 --> 03:15.227
You have been working on
your crusts, young man.

03:15.229 --> 03:17.563
  Hey! Happy birthday, Clarence!

03:17.565 --> 03:19.998
Vu! You're just in time.

03:20.000 --> 03:23.235
Come on, buddy. Let me show you
all around party central.

03:23.237 --> 03:24.703
  Over here, we got the chips,
     set up by yours truly.

03:24.705 --> 03:25.971
And I think we've got some dip
     somewhere,

03:25.973 --> 03:27.573
   but I'll worry
  about that later.

03:27.575 --> 03:29.675
   Psst! Wasn't expecting to see
               you today, Vu.

03:29.677 --> 03:32.411
 Oh, yeah. My brother got lice,
   so our trip got cancelled.

03:32.413 --> 03:34.046
                No, I mean --
                Wait, what?!

03:34.048 --> 03:36.048
Usually, that's where I go
  to the bathroom.

03:36.050 --> 03:38.884
 Clarence, look what I made you!
I mixed together a bunch of crud

03:38.886 --> 03:41.587
 from my yard and under my sink
  so we could glack each other,

03:41.589 --> 03:43.488
      like on "Stinky Boys
          Courthouse."

03:43.490 --> 03:46.325
                            Ugh!
             What?!

03:46.327 --> 03:48.594
          Whoa! Gross.

03:48.596 --> 03:50.596
I bet you can't glack me.

03:50.598 --> 03:52.931
         Yeah, I can. I'm gonna.

03:52.933 --> 03:55.434
                     S'up, guys?
       Oh, hey, Chelsea!

03:55.436 --> 03:57.569
         Oh, and Kimby!
          Oh, uh, um...

03:57.571 --> 03:59.338
         Let me show you
      where the chips are.

03:59.340 --> 04:00.906
      Everyone loves chips.

04:00.908 --> 04:02.774
Well, I guess it's just a couple
    more people.

04:02.776 --> 04:07.512
  [ Laughter and conversation ]

04:07.514 --> 04:09.915
I hope you like punch, because I
        sat in the punch,

04:09.917 --> 04:11.750
        and I like punch
        and now I'm wet.

04:11.752 --> 04:13.452
      Percy! What are you doing?

04:13.454 --> 04:15.420
           You need a party hat.

04:15.422 --> 04:18.123
      Party hat. Party hat.
           Party hat.

04:18.125 --> 04:22.361
       No more party hats.
Party pat. Party pat. Party pat.

04:22.363 --> 04:25.130
So, how do you guys know
      Clarence?

04:25.132 --> 04:26.798
           Seriously!

04:26.800 --> 04:29.401
  And this is before I learned
      how to use the potty.

04:29.403 --> 04:31.136
  I had to take a lot of baths
           back then.

04:31.138 --> 04:34.740
   And this is after I went to
   the bathroom all by myself.

04:34.742 --> 04:37.476
                Hi, Clarence!
         Prepare to get glacked!

04:37.478 --> 04:40.312
           [ Laughs ]
        Sumo, you missed.

04:40.314 --> 04:42.981
Ohhh! My party dress!

04:42.983 --> 04:44.483
 What is this stuff?

04:44.485 --> 04:46.318
              What?

04:46.320 --> 04:47.653
     Aw, this party stinks!

04:47.655 --> 04:49.288
  Tell me about it!

04:49.290 --> 04:51.657
I haven't had one chance to talk
to Clarence all day.

04:51.659 --> 04:53.225
    It's like we don't exist.

04:53.227 --> 04:55.093
    What are you doing here?

04:55.095 --> 04:56.928
 Uh, I was invited.

04:56.930 --> 04:58.397
      Ooh! Pie!

04:58.399 --> 05:02.000
      Mm! Wow!
 That's pretty good!

05:02.002 --> 05:03.402
  Did you make it?

05:03.404 --> 05:05.170
        It's not for you!

05:05.172 --> 05:08.240
 Clarence just doesn't remember
      how sweet the pie is.

05:08.242 --> 05:10.342
       I gotta remind him.

05:10.344 --> 05:12.511
      There you go, Kimby.
          Good as new.

05:12.513 --> 05:14.946
All right. All right.
You've had your moment!

05:14.948 --> 05:18.417
   Hey, buddy. Are you finally
  ready for a nice, hot slice?

05:18.419 --> 05:20.085
      Um, okay.

05:20.087 --> 05:21.787
                 Open wide.

05:21.789 --> 05:25.190
        Okay, party kids.
       Time for presents!

05:25.192 --> 05:27.025
 What?! Wait for me!

05:27.027 --> 05:28.927
              But -- But, pie.

05:28.929 --> 05:32.597
  You're gonna hide behind this
 tree and stand really straight

05:32.599 --> 05:34.333
           like this.

05:34.335 --> 05:35.434
     Okay, good, good, good.

05:35.436 --> 05:36.501
     There you go, Chelsea.

05:36.503 --> 05:38.203
  Everyone else, you all good?

05:38.205 --> 05:40.806
                I'm gone now.

05:40.808 --> 05:42.874
    It's gonna be so perfect.

05:42.876 --> 05:46.545
    Back to regular Clarence
      and my regular life.

05:46.547 --> 05:48.447
          [ Giggling ]

05:48.449 --> 05:50.315
  I'm just going about my day.

05:50.317 --> 05:51.650
         ALL: Surprise!

05:51.652 --> 05:54.186
     Oh, my gosh. You guys.

05:54.188 --> 05:58.123
 You went through all this whole
       thing just for me?

05:58.125 --> 06:00.992
                    [ Grumbles ]
It's not even a surprise.

06:00.994 --> 06:05.230
      And, inside this bag,
        is another bag...

06:05.232 --> 06:07.999
        from Filzer Corp.

06:08.001 --> 06:10.335
             Yeah. It's my dad's
         pharmaceutical company.

06:10.337 --> 06:13.505
         Oh, thanks, Vu.

06:13.507 --> 06:16.408
     What's taking so long?

06:16.410 --> 06:19.311
     Man, how did we end up last
         in line? It's not fair.

06:21.248 --> 06:23.515
 What's it gonna be?
 What's it gonna be?

06:23.517 --> 06:25.484
         Hey, Clarence.
     You wanna play some --

06:25.486 --> 06:28.754
I got Ding! Dong! Donkey!

06:28.756 --> 06:30.689
Thank you so much, Gilben!

06:30.691 --> 06:32.257
  Oh! Let's play it right now!

06:32.259 --> 06:35.594
          [ Laughing ]

06:35.596 --> 06:37.062
This is the stupidest game ever.

06:37.064 --> 06:39.197
 I've hated this game ever since
          I was little.

06:39.199 --> 06:40.565
          [ Squawking ]

06:40.567 --> 06:45.570
     Oh, Belson.
  Come and get it.

06:45.572 --> 06:47.506
          [ Giggling ]

06:47.508 --> 06:50.108
     There you go. You won.

06:50.110 --> 06:53.412
Man, forget this! He obviously
doesn't care if we're here.

06:53.414 --> 06:56.281
    Just look at him, basking in
          the glow and affection

06:56.283 --> 06:59.418
          of his "real" friends.
Let's go have our own party.

06:59.420 --> 07:01.186
                 Fine by me!

07:02.956 --> 07:05.924
        � Happy birthday!
        Happy birthday! �

07:05.926 --> 07:08.794
        � Happy birthday,
        birthday time! �

07:08.796 --> 07:12.731
          Oh, my gosh. Clarence!
   Look what you forgot to open.

07:12.733 --> 07:15.133
   Oh, boy! What could it be?

07:15.135 --> 07:19.638
 It's probably a shaving kit or
        rain boots or --

07:19.640 --> 07:22.140
           Aaaaaaaah!

07:22.142 --> 07:25.277
          Oh, my gosh!
   Oh, boy! Oh, boy! Oh, boy!

07:25.279 --> 07:26.978
      A bike! I got a bike!

07:26.980 --> 07:30.048
       There's two wheels,
      two handlebars, pegs.

07:30.050 --> 07:32.317
 What do you think of it, Jeff?

07:32.319 --> 07:35.387
           Jeff? Sumo?

07:35.389 --> 07:37.956
            [ Gasps ]
             Oh, no!

07:37.958 --> 07:40.759
    He obviously likes all those
                 other jerks

07:40.761 --> 07:42.160
          more than he likes us.

07:42.162 --> 07:44.930
     Yeah. Vu gets him a bag
    and he gets all excited.

07:44.932 --> 07:47.966
 Meanwhile, he doesn't even care
     that we worked so hard

07:47.968 --> 07:50.469
     making these extremely
        thoughtful gifts.

07:50.471 --> 07:52.170
               You know what?

07:52.172 --> 07:55.173
     If he doesn't want 'em,
       I say we chuck 'em.

07:55.175 --> 07:56.808
     Yeah. Yeah!

07:56.810 --> 07:58.910
           Forget you, Clarence!

07:58.912 --> 08:02.247
 Yeah, do it, Jeff.

08:02.249 --> 08:05.016
          No, no, no. You first!
              It was your idea!

08:05.018 --> 08:07.152
All right. On the count of
       three.

08:07.154 --> 08:12.090
    1, 2, 3, 4...

08:12.092 --> 08:14.359
 Listen up, friends. This ain't
          no real party

08:14.361 --> 08:16.862
     without Jeff and Sumo.
     Who am I even kidding?

08:16.864 --> 08:19.264
    So, don't play any games.
      Don't touch any cake.

08:19.266 --> 08:22.534
         No soup, okay?
Not until I get my friends back.

08:22.536 --> 08:24.202
        Up, up and awa-.

08:24.204 --> 08:25.804
        [ Creak, grunt ]

08:25.806 --> 08:28.306
       Okay. That's okay.
       I got my helmet on.

08:28.308 --> 08:30.175
      I'll just try again.

08:30.177 --> 08:32.277
    Can't really get the hang
            of this.

08:32.279 --> 08:33.945
             What do we do now?

08:33.947 --> 08:36.615
 Chozo, it's your time to shine.

08:36.616 --> 08:39.351
          [ Groaning ]

08:48.795 --> 08:53.498
    57, 58, 60...

08:53.500 --> 08:56.234
           Aaaaaaaah!

08:56.236 --> 08:58.570
              Clarence, wh-what
             are you doing here?

08:58.572 --> 09:02.574
Yeah. Are you done making out
with all your new best friends?

09:02.576 --> 09:05.010
       Guys, I'm so sorry.

09:05.012 --> 09:07.379
 I was all excited about seeing
           everyone...

09:07.381 --> 09:08.914
      Oh, geez.

09:08.916 --> 09:11.349
     ...and opening presents
    and eating chips, but --

09:11.351 --> 09:14.052
  but I can't have my birthday
      without my best buds.

09:14.054 --> 09:16.254
I'm the worst bestie bud.

09:16.256 --> 09:20.825
Now I'm just here on this
garbage rock where I belong.

09:20.827 --> 09:23.194
        No, no, Clarence.
          We're sorry.

09:23.196 --> 09:25.597
 We didn't think anyone else was
        gonna come today,

09:25.599 --> 09:28.033
  and we were excited to spend
     your birthday with you.

09:28.035 --> 09:30.435
            Then all these other
       bozos show up, and, well,

09:30.437 --> 09:33.705
    I guess I just really wanted
   to goof around with my buddy.

09:33.707 --> 09:35.273
              Yeah.

09:35.275 --> 09:37.208
    Ah, you guys!

09:37.210 --> 09:40.745
No matter what, you guys
are always my bestie buds.

09:40.747 --> 09:42.948
                  Oh, man.

09:42.950 --> 09:45.183
Okay, Clarence. Let go.
Too tight. Too tight!

09:45.185 --> 09:47.118
   No. I'm never gonna let go.

09:47.120 --> 09:49.354
Then you're gonna get glacked!

09:49.356 --> 09:51.523
         Hey! You guys.

09:51.525 --> 09:54.759
    Okay, who wants a whale?

09:54.761 --> 09:56.795
        Oh, um, ooh, um.

09:56.797 --> 09:59.464
    Oh, all right! Go, Chozo!

09:59.466 --> 10:00.966
            Whoo-hoo!

10:00.968 --> 10:03.101
Um, you want quarters or
  something, or --

10:03.103 --> 10:05.870
              Girl:
 Hey! Belson's eating the cake!

10:05.872 --> 10:09.307
          [ Laughing ]
        Oh, that was fun!

10:09.309 --> 10:12.077
            My cake!
            My party!

10:12.079 --> 10:14.980
    Just a little more bite.

10:14.982 --> 10:17.816
          I love cake!
        Just one more --

10:17.818 --> 10:19.818
            They're coming back!

10:23.256 --> 10:26.257
  Light those candles, and grab
      some wrapping paper.

10:26.259 --> 10:28.727
          This party is
      just getting started.

10:28.729 --> 10:30.428
      You sure you want to
         do it this way?

10:30.430 --> 10:32.964
   Uh, wrapping up a bike you
     already, kind of, used?

10:32.966 --> 10:34.599
         Sure, I'm sure.

10:34.601 --> 10:36.735
  But, Clarence, we've already
         seen your bike.

10:36.737 --> 10:39.004
Nuh-unh. You didn't see my bike.

10:39.006 --> 10:41.773
  Okay, little man.
   It's all yours!

10:41.775 --> 10:43.742
  Ooh! What is it? What is it?

10:43.744 --> 10:46.011
      Oh, man. It could be
         a baseball bat.

10:46.013 --> 10:48.279
    Oh, maybe it's a stapler.

10:48.281 --> 10:50.515
             A bike!
     Look at the handlebars!

10:50.517 --> 10:53.685
   Look at these wheels, huh!
       It even has peg --

10:53.687 --> 10:55.020
              Huh?

10:55.022 --> 10:56.755
           [ Grunts ]
              Huh?

10:56.757 --> 10:58.957
          [ Screaming ]

10:58.959 --> 11:02.427
          Oh, no! Chad!
      What's following you?

11:05.265 --> 11:07.866
        � Early to bed �

11:07.868 --> 11:11.803
        � Early to rise �

11:11.805 --> 11:15.440
       � Picking my nose �

11:18.011 --> 11:20.745
                     ��

11:22.282 --> 11:26.685
           Young Chad:
There we were between the ground
         and the sky...

11:26.687 --> 11:28.953
       hoping that the sun
         would come back

11:28.955 --> 11:31.322
 and that the opossums wouldn't.
        [ All shivering ]

11:31.324 --> 11:33.825
       But when we finally
        reached the top,

11:33.827 --> 11:36.327
      -it was all worth it.
      -It was all worth it.

11:36.329 --> 11:38.163
       We carved our names
          in that tree,

11:38.165 --> 11:40.198
   and we've been best friends
           ever since.

11:40.200 --> 11:41.966
              -Wow!
              -Wow!

11:41.968 --> 11:43.535
Since when did it snow
    in Aberdale?

11:43.537 --> 11:45.203
                Tell me more
             about your friends.

11:45.205 --> 11:48.640
               Where are they?
             Tell me everything.

11:48.642 --> 11:51.142
        Well,
 Jere went to Nam...

11:51.144 --> 11:52.744
where her parents moved.

11:52.746 --> 11:57.015
And Gooner, I like to think
he's still watching over me.

11:57.017 --> 11:58.917
He works in surveillance.
    [ Chuckles ]

11:58.919 --> 12:00.418
                Just like me
             and Sumo and Jeff.

12:00.420 --> 12:01.886
               Oh, tape more,
                 tape more!

12:01.888 --> 12:03.555
   Ah, man alive.

12:03.557 --> 12:06.091
Thanks for helping me
 hang signs, guys.
        Sumo: No problem.

12:06.093 --> 12:09.194
      One day, we're gonna carve
       our names into that tree,

12:09.196 --> 12:11.162
    and we'll be best tree buds,
                    too.

12:11.164 --> 12:13.398
I'm afraid it's too late,
     little man.

12:13.400 --> 12:17.869
              "Notification --
           fungus tree removal."

12:17.871 --> 12:19.204
Yeah, tree's infected.

12:19.206 --> 12:21.339
 That's why they're
cutting it down tomorrow.

12:21.341 --> 12:22.674
Well, it's like they say.

12:22.676 --> 12:26.044
You don't know what you got
   till it's gone.

12:26.046 --> 12:27.612
Well, see you at home!

12:27.614 --> 12:28.913
                    Ohh.

12:28.915 --> 12:31.750
        [ All munching ]

12:31.752 --> 12:35.420
  Mom, can you pass
    the, uh, ham?

12:35.422 --> 12:38.056
            Oh. Mmm!
   Sorry, hon, it's all gone.

12:38.058 --> 12:40.625
              [ Groans softly ]

12:40.627 --> 12:42.861
    Wooly: <i> This sale's headed</i>
        <i> for extinction!</i>

12:42.863 --> 12:47.265
 <i> So buy your discount mattress</i>
       <i> before it's gone!</i>

12:47.267 --> 12:48.566
                     ��

12:48.568 --> 12:50.268
              Ohh.

12:50.270 --> 12:52.103
   Hey, Clarence,
want to play a board game?

12:52.105 --> 12:53.104
              Heck, yeah, I do!

12:53.106 --> 12:54.939
            [ Gasps ]
          Where's Sumo?

12:54.941 --> 12:56.541
   Oh, he's gone.

12:56.543 --> 12:57.909
              Ohh.

12:57.911 --> 12:59.811
        -To the bathroom.
              -Oh.

12:59.813 --> 13:00.912
              -Aah!
             -What?

13:00.914 --> 13:02.280
         Come on, Jeff.

13:02.282 --> 13:04.983
        -Let's go, Sumo!
          -[ Laughing ]

13:04.985 --> 13:06.217
                  Go where?

13:06.219 --> 13:08.286
     [ <i> Whispered gibberish</i> ]

13:08.288 --> 13:10.822
                     ��

13:12.959 --> 13:16.761
 This is the tallest tree in the
 neighborhood, maybe the world.

13:16.763 --> 13:18.663
    And tomorrow,
they're cutting it down.

13:18.665 --> 13:20.999
If we're gonna climb it,
 tonight's our shot.

13:21.001 --> 13:22.400
                  Climb it?

13:22.402 --> 13:24.135
    I thought we were just gonna
              pay our respects.

13:24.137 --> 13:26.004
I came for the fungus!

13:26.006 --> 13:27.972
           -Ha ha! Ah.
           -[ Laughs ]

13:27.974 --> 13:30.809
       Alternate idea -- There's
     a parking garage next door.

13:30.811 --> 13:32.811
Why don't we just walk
     to the top?

13:32.813 --> 13:34.813
  Boop, yeah. Boop.
     [ Laughs ]

13:34.815 --> 13:38.149
                 Ugh. Fine.
But I don't want to be out late.

13:38.151 --> 13:40.118
     [ Grunts ]

13:40.120 --> 13:41.686
           [ Squeak! ]

13:41.688 --> 13:42.987
      [ Farts ]

13:42.989 --> 13:44.355
        We're gonna be out late.

13:44.357 --> 13:45.590
        [ All grunting ]

13:45.592 --> 13:49.260
    [ Straining ]
Just a little bit higher.

13:49.262 --> 13:51.362
         That's as high
          as I can get.

13:51.364 --> 13:53.331
        [ All grunting ]

13:53.333 --> 13:56.134
   That was lower,
but I appreciate the effort.

13:56.136 --> 13:57.635
              I don't even want
                 to be here.

13:57.637 --> 13:59.370
      Well, just help us up
            at least.

13:59.372 --> 14:01.773
             -Fine!
           -[ Grunts ]

14:02.309 --> 14:05.310
            Whew!
      Come on up, best bud.

14:05.312 --> 14:07.312
     Weather's really great
            up here.

14:07.314 --> 14:09.848
    You can sign my name for me.
                 Good night.

14:09.850 --> 14:11.883
          [ Rustling ]

14:11.885 --> 14:13.952
        [ Button clicks ]

14:13.954 --> 14:15.820
        Nocturnal animal!

14:15.822 --> 14:17.989
                [ Shrieking ]

14:17.991 --> 14:19.891
              -Wow!
             -Uh...

14:19.893 --> 14:20.825
                    What?

14:20.827 --> 14:23.661
              Jeff,
    you have climber's arms!

14:23.663 --> 14:24.562
                    I do?

14:24.564 --> 14:26.631
           Wow! I-I had no idea.

14:26.633 --> 14:29.367
           You'd think that Sumo
   would be the best at climbing

14:29.369 --> 14:31.069
             [Chuckles] but no.
                [ Chuckles ]

14:31.071 --> 14:34.138
      Believe me, I'm as shocked
                 as you are.
 [ Growls ]

14:34.140 --> 14:36.207
            Well, let's do this.

14:36.209 --> 14:38.910
          -[ Whooping ]
          -[ Grunting ]

14:38.912 --> 14:41.546
                     ��

14:49.923 --> 14:50.922
                   Ha ha!

14:50.924 --> 14:52.690
          [ Whooping ]

14:52.692 --> 14:55.760
          I'm doing it!
     I'm actually doing it!

14:55.762 --> 14:56.761
    [ Muttering ]

14:56.763 --> 14:59.097
     [ <i> Whispered gibberish</i> ]
    Huh?

15:01.568 --> 15:04.502
  [ Grunts ]
       [ Birds chirping ]

15:07.007 --> 15:08.473
        Huh?

15:17.851 --> 15:19.617
          [ Crackling ]

15:21.721 --> 15:26.124
        Ohh.
I feel so sore but so alive.

15:26.126 --> 15:28.059
            You really did it up
                 out there.

15:28.061 --> 15:29.694
                 Gimme five.

15:29.696 --> 15:33.731
            Uh, guys.
I'm not so sure about this tree.

15:33.733 --> 15:35.633
          I keep seeing
       these weird faces.

15:35.635 --> 15:38.636
That's probably just the fungus
  warping the bark.

15:38.638 --> 15:41.205
                Who made you
            the big tree expert?

15:41.207 --> 15:42.473
    [ Grunting ]

15:42.475 --> 15:44.409
It's all in the arms,
        baby,

15:44.411 --> 15:46.945
something you wouldn't
know anything about.

15:46.947 --> 15:49.614
                 That's it!
      You want a piece of this?!

15:49.616 --> 15:52.784
  [ Grunts ] Sure.
How about some arm wrestling?

15:52.786 --> 15:54.786
               Ah.
     These are the quarrels

15:54.788 --> 15:57.989
   that only true friendships
        can bring about.

15:57.991 --> 15:59.958
        [ Both grunting ]

15:59.960 --> 16:01.960
           Okay, guys.
         That's enough.

16:01.962 --> 16:03.928
              Both:
     Clarence, we're hungry!

16:03.930 --> 16:05.296
               Oh.

16:05.298 --> 16:07.131
             Ta-da!

16:07.133 --> 16:10.335
 I thought if we were on a break
         from climbing,

16:10.337 --> 16:12.236
    we could play "Jumungo."

16:12.238 --> 16:17.408
  "The only game where players
         climb a tree."

16:17.410 --> 16:18.710
           [ Groans ]

16:24.784 --> 16:27.485
                     ��

16:27.487 --> 16:29.487
        All right, guys.
          Big decision.

16:29.489 --> 16:32.256
       Which way do we go?

16:32.258 --> 16:33.491
  Isn't it obvious?

16:33.493 --> 16:34.993
         We should ask the tree.

16:34.995 --> 16:38.696
Sumo, are you sure you didn't
eat any of the fungus?

16:38.698 --> 16:41.566
     [ <i> Whispered gibberish</i> ]

16:43.336 --> 16:45.236
     We should go this way.

16:46.806 --> 16:49.173
             Really?
   Is that what you guys want?

16:49.175 --> 16:51.009
       It looks so scary.

16:51.011 --> 16:52.844
        [ Wind howling ]

16:52.846 --> 16:56.014
[ Hoarsely ] Surely tree gnomes
  know how to cook.

16:56.016 --> 16:57.382
        I'm still hungry.

16:57.384 --> 16:59.384
       [ Gruffly ] I told you we
   should've gone the other way.

16:59.386 --> 17:03.855
        Fellas, check out
      this goofy tree face.

17:03.857 --> 17:05.223
           [ Laughs ]

17:05.224 --> 17:06.958
           [ Screams ]

17:06.960 --> 17:07.992
         [ Both scream ]

17:07.993 --> 17:09.359
  Finally! Snacks!

17:09.362 --> 17:12.663
 I'm starting to see why they're
         cutting this tree down.

17:12.665 --> 17:14.632
              -Aah!
          -Wait for me!

17:14.634 --> 17:17.367
              Whoa!
          [ Thudding ]

17:17.369 --> 17:20.104
        [ All screaming ]

17:22.642 --> 17:24.208
          [ Grunting ]

17:24.210 --> 17:25.410
Clarence, pull me up!

17:25.412 --> 17:27.045
                    Yeah,
           after you pull me up!

17:27.047 --> 17:30.214
          [ Straining ]
 I can't hold on to both of you!

17:30.216 --> 17:32.850
  Save me! You need
my strong climber's arms!

17:32.852 --> 17:34.318
         I can talk to the tree!

17:34.320 --> 17:35.653
     You're both my friends.

17:35.655 --> 17:37.889
If you don't decide,
  we'll both fall.

17:37.891 --> 17:40.158
      The tree got us into this.

17:40.160 --> 17:41.759
          The tree shall decide.

17:41.761 --> 17:44.095
     [ <i> Whispered gibberish</i> ]

17:44.097 --> 17:47.565
          [ Speaking gibberish ]

17:47.567 --> 17:50.568
               The tree says,
                  "Let go."

17:50.570 --> 17:53.604
              -No!
             -Sumo!

17:54.908 --> 17:56.240
       Ha ha.

17:56.242 --> 17:57.942
    That was fun.

17:57.944 --> 17:59.710
                 [ Grunts ]

17:59.712 --> 18:01.412
        [ Both panting ]

18:01.414 --> 18:03.414
He sacrificed himself.

18:03.416 --> 18:05.383
It won't be in vain.

18:05.385 --> 18:07.685
                     ��

18:08.521 --> 18:10.455
                Hey, Jeffrey!
                 Pull me up!

18:10.457 --> 18:12.356
             -Jeff?
     -[ Breathing heavily ]

18:12.358 --> 18:14.392
              [ Grunts ] Jeff?

18:14.394 --> 18:17.128
               Why'd you stop
                  climbing?

18:17.130 --> 18:20.431
They say that air is thinner
at higher altitudes.

18:20.433 --> 18:22.233
    [ Chuckles ]
       Ironic.

18:22.235 --> 18:26.237
I have climber's arms
but a groundling's lungs.

18:26.239 --> 18:27.705
     [ Shivers ]

18:27.707 --> 18:30.775
      [ Gasps ]
 I see...the light.

18:30.777 --> 18:33.411
                The sunrise!
        We're almost at the top!

18:33.413 --> 18:35.780
     [ Coughs ]
    I can't move.

18:35.782 --> 18:38.249
         Then I'll move for you.

18:38.251 --> 18:40.485
                     ��

18:40.487 --> 18:42.787
I'm holding you back,
      Clarence.

18:42.789 --> 18:44.956
     -You have to leave me.
              -No.

18:44.958 --> 18:49.060
  I don't want to be like Chad
      and Jere and Gooner.

18:49.062 --> 18:52.630
  They grew up and -- and went
    in different directions.

18:52.632 --> 18:54.999
  We have to do this together.
              Aah!

18:55.001 --> 18:56.467
                     ��

18:56.469 --> 18:59.337
              Jeff!

18:59.339 --> 19:01.506
         Oh.

19:01.508 --> 19:03.574
   That was weird.

19:03.576 --> 19:05.276
        [ Wind howling ]

19:05.278 --> 19:07.612
         <i> Keep climbing.</i>

19:07.614 --> 19:09.313
            [ Gasps ]
         Who said that?

19:09.315 --> 19:12.016
        Tree-fungus face?
            You talk?

19:12.018 --> 19:15.253
<i> You know, any day now,</i>
 <i> the sun will rise,</i>

19:15.255 --> 19:16.687
<i> and then I'll be gone.</i>

19:16.689 --> 19:19.190
<i> You got to climb me,</i>
     <i> Clarence.</i>

19:19.192 --> 19:21.759
          Yeah. O-Okay.

19:21.761 --> 19:24.595
          [ Grunting ]

19:25.665 --> 19:30.134
        <i> Yes!</i>
<i> Do it for your friends.</i>

19:30.136 --> 19:35.106
<i> You want your friends to be</i>
<i> friends forever, don't you?</i>

19:35.108 --> 19:40.144
  Yeah, me and Jeff and Sumo --
        friends forever.

19:40.146 --> 19:41.345
      <i> And me.</i>

19:41.347 --> 19:47.018
<i> I'll be your friend, too,</i>
      <i> forever.</i>

19:47.020 --> 19:48.186
        <i> Yes.</i>

19:48.188 --> 19:50.955
     [ Echoing ]
  <i> Welcome, my boy.</i>

19:50.957 --> 19:52.690
 <i> You made it here.</i>

19:52.692 --> 19:55.293
<i> Now sign the contract.</i>

19:55.295 --> 19:56.527
  <i> Oh, I mean bark.</i>

19:56.529 --> 19:58.129
                  Uh, okay.

19:58.131 --> 20:01.199
[ Normal voice ] <i> Carve your name</i>
<i> into me like Chad did.</i>

20:01.201 --> 20:05.069
<i> Remember -- full legal name,</i>
  <i> middle initial.</i>

20:05.071 --> 20:09.073
             <i> -Yes!</i>
       -Wow! Just like us.

20:10.877 --> 20:12.543
[ Echoing ] <i> Come on.</i>

20:12.545 --> 20:14.245
<i> What are you waiting for?</i>

20:14.247 --> 20:16.981
 <i> Don't want to miss</i>
    <i> your chance.</i>

20:16.983 --> 20:20.585
<i> You don't know what you got</i>
 <i> till they're gone.</i>

20:20.587 --> 20:22.720
                    Wait.
              What did you say?

20:22.722 --> 20:26.557
[ Normal voice ] <i> Um, oh, yeah.</i>
<i> What you got till it's gone.</i>

20:26.559 --> 20:28.659
 You said, "till <i> they're</i> gone."

20:28.661 --> 20:31.262
   <i> No, I didn't.</i>

20:32.398 --> 20:33.831
          I was wrong.

20:33.833 --> 20:35.866
 I don't need to carve our names
        on top of a tree

20:35.868 --> 20:37.068
     to be friends forever.

20:37.070 --> 20:39.070
        I just need to be
         where they are.

20:39.072 --> 20:40.905
                   <i> What?!</i>
             <i> But you're here...</i>

20:40.907 --> 20:42.573
             [Echoing] <i> with me.</i>

20:42.575 --> 20:43.741
            Noooooo!

20:43.743 --> 20:45.409
              [ <i> Laughs evilly</i> ]

20:45.411 --> 20:48.713
         <i> You made a bad choice,</i>
                 <i> Clarence.</i>

20:48.715 --> 20:50.514
          <i> Why did you leave me?</i>

20:50.516 --> 20:52.216
              [ <i> Laughs evilly</i> ]

20:52.218 --> 20:53.384
              Aah!

20:53.386 --> 20:55.720
  Who are you?
                    Name's Jere.

20:55.722 --> 20:58.589
But I thought you were
     in the Nam.

20:58.591 --> 21:02.760
   I was -- Namaste, New Mexico,
        just a few hours' drive.

21:02.762 --> 21:04.028
             Hey, bud, you okay?

21:04.030 --> 21:06.097
              Telling you guys
        about climbing this tree

21:06.099 --> 21:08.966
        made me realize I should
   call these dudes to catch up.

21:08.968 --> 21:10.268
   When you didn't come home,

21:10.270 --> 21:12.069
        Gooner here knew
     just where to find you.

21:12.071 --> 21:15.139
Wow! So you're all still
bestest tree buddies?

21:15.141 --> 21:17.041
            Um, uh...

21:17.043 --> 21:19.143
        Wow.
   That's awesome!

21:19.145 --> 21:21.612
  Sorry we didn't get to carve
      our names at the top

21:21.614 --> 21:22.947
        like you wanted,
            Clarence.

21:22.949 --> 21:24.315
              Oh, that's okay.

21:24.317 --> 21:26.617
       It's just a dumb old pile
              of twigs anyway.

21:26.619 --> 21:29.387
   Well, how about we go home
       and play "Jumungo"?

21:29.389 --> 21:33.958
   [ Menacingly ] Don't you kids
            ever play "Jumungo".

21:33.960 --> 21:36.794
      Now, let's watch that tree
              get chopped down.

21:36.796 --> 21:38.596
         Jeff: Oh, man,
      they're almost there.

21:38.598 --> 21:39.964
    That thing's coming down.

21:39.966 --> 21:45.002
    <i> I had 74 little friends</i>
         <i> who loved me,</i>

21:45.004 --> 21:47.405
       <i> who cared for me.</i>

21:47.407 --> 21:51.509
    <i> They said they'd never,</i>
        <i> never leave me.</i>

21:51.511 --> 21:54.178
        [ All cheering ]

21:57.917 --> 21:59.750
        � Early to bed �

22:01.287 --> 22:03.421
        � Early to rise �

22:04.924 --> 22:07.825
       � Picking my nose �
